Chapter 13

The dragon was even more fearsome than Kion had imagined. Its scales were as hard as steel, and its fiery breath could melt stone. But Kion was not one to back down from a challenge.

He engaged the dragon in battle, drawing upon all the skills and strengths he had acquired on his journey. The battle was long and grueling, and at times it seemed as though Kion might be defeated.

But Kion refused to give up. He pressed on, drawing upon his inner courage and strength, until at last he emerged victorious, vanquishing the dragon and freeing the nearby villages from its tyranny.
